        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-17T21:18:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-17T21:18:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-17T11:48:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-17T11:48:00Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system south of the Bight extends a ridge over SA. The high will slowly move east over the weekend ahead of a cold front which will slip to the south of SA and weaken. The high will remain near stationary in the southern Tasman Sea, maintaining a ridge across the state early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
